Verify your data in OneDrive storage
 
OneDrive for Business client enables you to sync important files between yo=
ur computer and the cloud. With this you can now access your files from any=
 of your managed device, which can be your computer, your mobile device, or=
 even through the OneDrive for Business Web. 
 
OneDrive enables you to Share files with your team members 
 and collaborate. OneDrive acces=
s is enabled only from Infosys managed devices. To avoid access issues when=
 not in Infosys network, use Internet explorer for better experience.
 
You can work on your synced files directly in file explorer and access your=
 files even when you=E2=80=99re offline. These changes will sync with your =
OneDrive storage whenever you=E2=80=99re online. If you add, change or dele=
te a file/folder in your OneDrive folder(D:\OneDrive - Infosys Limited), th=
e same process [addition/change/deletion] will be replicated on your OneDri=
ve cloud and vice versa. Only files which are in OneDrive folder (D:\OneDri=
ve - Infosys Limited) will be in sync with OneDrive cloud .
 
PST=E2=80=99s connected to outlook won=E2=80=99t sync to ODFB and will crea=
te multiple versions of the PST every time you close outlook. This will ult=
imately end up in consuming entire 5TB of ODFB storage. Once storage is ful=
l, none of the changes made will get updated. Always keep your active PST o=
utside OneDrive folder to avoid OneDrive space issue.
 
Following these few simple steps during system changewill help avoid data loss =
and verify that the data is synced with OneDrive storage. During data sync =
folder structure gets created first and then file sync starts .Do not stop =
sync unless you have verified that all files are synced and present on OneD=
rive cloud and data size on cloud storage matches with local OneDrive folde=
r.
 
Please make sure to follow below steps to verify all your data are in sync =
with OneDrive storage. 
 
1.	Access OneDrive Web   and check if all your data =
(check specifically for files ) are present under main folders.
2.	Cross check your Data size on cloud storage matches with local OneDrive =
folder from OneDrive Settings >> Account tab 
 
                           
3.	Go to Manage Storage option  in above settings  and you can  see the sto=
rage metric of your data usage 
 
